" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/15.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2401" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/15-800x586.jpg" alt="Material Design Coming Soon Page 1" width="800" height="586" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/15-800x586.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/15-400x293.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/15-768x563.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/15.jpg 1302w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/14.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2402" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/14-800x553.jpg" alt="Material Design Coming Soon Page 3" width="800" height="553" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/14-800x553.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/14-400x276.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/14-768x531.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/14.jpg 1504w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/material-design-coming-soon-page-themes/">New Material Design Inspired Coming Soon Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://www.seedprod.com/material-design-coming-soon-page-themes/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2399";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"How to FTP into WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 28 Oct 2016 14:49:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2384";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:530:"<p>Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to ftp into WordPress and a walkthrough of the WordPress file and directory structure incase you ever need to upload a file or modify a directory or file. If you don&#8217;t already have a preferred FTP client I recommend Filezilla, This ftp client is free and works on [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/">How to FTP into WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6011:"<p>Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to ftp into WordPress and a walkthrough of the WordPress file and directory structure incase you ever need to upload a file or modify a directory or file.</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t already have a preferred FTP client I recommend <a href="https://filezilla-project.org/">Filezilla</a>, This ftp client is free and works on Windows, Macs, and Linux.</p>\n<div id="attachment_2385" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://filezilla-project.org/download.php?type=client"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2385" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/s_common-400x81.png" alt="filezilla" width="400" height="81" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/s_common-400x81.png 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/s_common.png 485w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Download Filezilla</p></div>\n<p><a href="https://filezilla-project.org/download.php?type=client">Download Filezilla</a></p>\n<p>If you are looking for a nice paid FTP for Macs I recommend <a href="https://panic.com/transmit/">Transmit</a> from Coda.</p>\n<p>After installing the ftp client the next thing you&#8217;ll want to do is get your ftp or sftp credentials from your web host. Contact your host if you do not have this information. They should provide you with a host ip or name, username, password and port number. Once you obtain this information you can then ftp into your WordPress site. Enter this info into the Filezilla Quick Connect screen.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/filezilla-ftp.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2387 size-large" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/filezilla-ftp-800x524.jpg" alt="filezilla-ftp" width="800" height="524" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/filezilla-ftp-800x524.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/filezilla-ftp-400x262.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/filezilla-ftp-768x503.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/filezilla-ftp.jpg 1086w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></p>\n<p>After successfully ftping into your host you&#8217;ll then will be in the root of you will need to browse to locate where WordPress is installed. Typically a web host will have the domain folders listed then once you click on the domain you will need to click on a folder that says <em>public</em>, <em>www</em>, or <em>wordpress</em> to locate where the root of WordPress is actually installed. Once you locate the root of WordPress you&#8217;ll see the files and folders in the screenshot below.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ftp-wordpress-directory.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2388 size-large" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ftp-wordpress-directory-800x425.jpg" alt="ftp-wordpress-directory" width="800" height="425" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ftp-wordpress-directory-800x425.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ftp-wordpress-directory-400x212.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ftp-wordpress-directory-768x408.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ftp-wordpress-directory.jpg 848w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></p>\n<p>The <strong>wp-config.php</strong> file is where you can modify your database credentials, turn on debugging for WordPress or modify any of the other setting WordPress allows in this file.</p>\n<p>The <strong>wp-content</strong> folder is where all your files live including your themes, plugins, uploads. Plugin&#8217;s may also put files in this folder for use as it relates to your site. All the other files and folder outside the wp-content folder and wp-config.php file are WordPress core files and you should never change, delete or modify the files and folders. Below is a screenshot of the wp-contet folder. If you ever need to manually update or edit a theme or plugin this is where you&#8217;ll do it.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2391" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example-800x793.jpg" alt="wp-content-folder-example" width="800" height="793" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example-800x793.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example-400x397.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example-768x762.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wp-content-folder-example.jpg 848w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></p>\n<p>As you can see the <strong>plugins</strong> folder contains all your plugin you have installed in WordPress. The <strong>themes</strong> folder has your installed themes. The <strong>uploads </strong>is where all your images and files you have uploaded through the media library live. Then you may see other folder that are plugin specific like<strong> wp-rocket-config</strong> and <strong>cache</strong> folder in the example able. The <strong>mu-plugins</strong> folder will only exists if you are running WordPress Multisite.</p>\n<p>So there you have it! One word of cation is make sure you always have a <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/backing-up-site-before-launch/">backup of WordPress</a> site before you go tinkering around via ftp just to be on the safe side.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/">How to FTP into WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2384";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"WordPress stuck in Maintenance Mode";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 26 Oct 2016 17:08:36 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2361";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:571:"<p>OK WordPress was updating itself, themes or plugins and something went wrong and now your WordPress site is stuck in Maintenance Mode with a message on the screen that reads &#8220;“Briefly unavailable for scheduled maintenance. Check back in a minute.” and you can not get into your wp-admin or view your site. Learn how to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/">WordPress stuck in Maintenance Mode</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1982:"<p>OK WordPress was updating itself, themes or plugins and something went wrong and now your WordPress site is stuck in Maintenance Mode with a message on the screen that reads &#8220;“<em>Briefly unavailable for scheduled maintenance. Check back in a minute.</em>” and you can not get into your wp-admin or view your site.</p>\n<p>Learn how to get out of Maintenance Mode when WordPress gets stuck. Follow these steps to quickly solve the issue.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/">FTP into your WordPress site</a> and look for a file called <strong>.maintenance</strong> in the WordPress root. (If you do not see this file make sure to adjust your setting in your ftp client and make hidden files visible.</li>\n<li>Delete this file.</li>\n</ol>\n<div id="attachment_2369" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1.jpg"><img class="wp-image-2369 size-medium" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1-400x377.jpg" width="400" height="377" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1-400x377.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/delete-maintenance-file-wordpress-1.jpg 539w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">How to get WordPress out of Maintenance Mode</p></div>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! WordPress should now be back to normal and serving your regular site.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/">Learn How to Customize the WordPress Maintenance Message</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/">WordPress stuck in Maintenance Mode</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-stuck-in-maintenance-mode/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2361";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"How to Create a Custom Maintenance Page in WordPress with Free Template";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:78:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 25 Oct 2016 15:26:50 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2344";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:664:"<p>WordPress has it&#8217;s own Maintenance Mode it goes into when it performs a core, themes or plugins updates. The picture above shows what you see when WordPress is performing these updates. What most people don&#8217;t know is that this is different from what a WordPress Maintenance Mode plugins would do. Learn more about the difference between WordPress&#8217;s [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/">How to Create a Custom Maintenance Page in WordPress with Free Template</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7044:"<div id="attachment_2346" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg"><img class="wp-image-2346 size-medium" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x324.jpg" alt="wordpress-maintenance-mode" width="400" height="324" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x324.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg 718w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Default WordPress Maintenance Page</p></div>\n<p>WordPress has it&#8217;s own Maintenance Mode it goes into when it performs a core, themes or plugins updates. The picture above shows what you see when WordPress is performing these updates. What most people don&#8217;t know is that this is different from what a WordPress <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/coming-soon/">Maintenance Mode plugins</a> would do. Learn more about the difference <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-maintenance-mode/">between WordPress&#8217;s built in maintenance mode vs what a maintenance mode plugin</a> does. In a nutshell a maintenance plugin will hide your site while you make changes, you still have access to the frontend and wp-admin backend, while the WordPress built in maintenance mode hides the entire site while the software itself is updating, no access to the frontend or backend. Therefore maintenance mode plugins won&#8217;t work when WordPress is doing it&#8217;s built in maintenance process. Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to customize the default maintenance message page which says &#8220;<em>Briefly unavailable for scheduled maintenance. Check back in a minute.</em>&#8221; to a custom html page and even how to collect emails on this page while your site is down.</p>\n<h2>How to Create a Custom WordPress Maintenance Mode Page</h2>\n<p>To create a custom maintenance message for WordPress you simply need to create a file called <strong>maintenance.php</strong> and upload this file to the root of your <strong>wp-content</strong> folder. (<a href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/">Learn how to ftp into WordPress</a>) This page will now be used when WordPress is performing updates to your site.</p>\n<div id="attachment_2349" style="width: 780px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-2349" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg" alt="Upload a file called maitenance.php to your wp-content folder." width="770" height="436" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page.jpg 770w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page-400x226.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/how-to-custom-wordpress-maintenence-page-768x435.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Upload a file called maintenance.php to your wp-content folder.</p></div>\n<p>One thing to note is you&#8217;ll want to make sure you put the correct http status code on this page so search engines know your site is in maintenance mode and will not index your maintenance page. This would be very bad for your SEO. To do this put this line of code on top of your <strong>maintenance.php</strong> file.<br />\n<code><br />\n&lt;?php<br />\nheader(''HTTP/1.1 503 Service Temporarily Unavailable'');<br />\nheader(''Status: 503 Service Temporarily Unavailable'');<br />\nheader(''Retry-After: 600'');<br />\n?&gt;<br />\n</code></p>\n<p>This tells search engines that your site is in unavailable and to try back in 10 minutes. WordPress core, themes and plugins updates usually only take a few seconds to update but we&#8217;ll put 10 minutes to be on the safe side. Below that http status code you can now add a custom message or html to create a better looking maintenance page or even add code to collect emails while your site is down.</p>\n<h2>Free Customizable WordPress Maintenance Mode Page Template</h2>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t know html we have included a download to our free maintenance mode template.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2354" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg" alt="custom wordpress maintenance mode page" width="916" height="737" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode.jpg 916w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-400x322.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-768x618.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-maintenance-mode-800x644.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 916px) 100vw, 916px" /></a></p>\n<p class="text-center">Get a free custom maintenance template for your WordPress website to use when WordPress is performing updates.</p>\n<div class="row">\n<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">\n<ul id="fcsp-features" class="list-unstyled">\n<li><strong>Features Include:</strong></li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-picture-o"></i>  Comes with 6 Background Images or Use Your Own</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-magic"></i>  Easily Customize the Logo, Headline and Description</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i>  Collect Emails with MailChimp</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-facebook-official"></i>  Display Links to Your Facebook, Twitter and Email Accounts</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-html5"></i>  Built with Bootstrap, HTML and CCS3</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-question-circle-o"></i>  Well Documented</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-seedprod btn-block" href="http://bit.ly/wordpress-maintenance-mode-template"><i class="fa fa-cloud-download"></i> Free Download</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Want to create a more customized maintenance page and collect email from different email providers? Checkout <a href="http://comingsoonpage.com/">http://comingsoonpage.com</a>, this builder creates custom html coming soon pages which can be repurposed for WordPress Maintenance Mode pages.</p>\n<p>If you are looking for a <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/coming-soon/">free WordPress Maintenance Mode Plugin</a> to use while you perform updates on your site instead check out <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/coming-soon/">Coming Soon Page &amp; Maintenance Mode by SeedProd</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/">How to Create a Custom Maintenance Page in WordPress with Free Template</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-maintenance-mode-page-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2344";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"How to Create a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress with Free Template";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-database-error-page-wordpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-database-error-page-wordpress/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 24 Oct 2016 17:48:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2314";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:662:"<p>* Scroll down to get our Free Custom WordPress Database Connection Error Template Have you ever visited a WordPress site or had your own site return a WordPress Database Error that says &#8220;Error Establishing A Database Connection&#8220;. This message can occur for several different reasons ranging from problems with your host to mistyped database credentials. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-database-error-page-wordpress/">How to Create a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress with Free Template</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7072:"<p><em>* Scroll down to get our Free Custom WordPress Database Connection Error Template</em></p>\n<div id="attachment_2319" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-connection-error-page-1.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2319" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-connection-error-page-1-400x274.jpg" alt="wordpress-database-connection-error-page" width="400" height="274" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-connection-error-page-1-400x274.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-connection-error-page-1-768x526.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-connection-error-page-1-800x548.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-connection-error-page-1.jpg 832w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Default WordPress Database Connection Error Page</p></div>\n<p>Have you ever visited a WordPress site or had your own site return a WordPress Database Error that says &#8220;<em>Error Establishing A Database Connection</em>&#8220;. This message can occur for several different reasons ranging from problems with your host to mistyped database credentials. Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to customize this message into something more useful for your visitors when they encounter this error.</p>\n<p>The image above shows the default WordPress connection error. Wouldn&#8217;t it be great to provide your visitors with a more attract message and maybe a way for visitors to leave their email so they can be notified when your site is back up? Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to accomplish both.</p>\n<h2>How to Create a Custom WordPress Database Error Page</h2>\n<p>The good news is that creating a WordPress Custom Database Connection Error Page is as simple as uploading a file named <strong>db-error.php</strong> to the root of your <strong>wp-content</strong> folder in WordPress. (<a href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-ftp-into-wordpress/">Learn how to ftp into WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/db-error-in-wp-content.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2322" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/db-error-in-wp-content.jpg" alt="db-error-in-wp-content" width="831" height="470" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/db-error-in-wp-content.jpg 831w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/db-error-in-wp-content-400x226.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/db-error-in-wp-content-768x434.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/db-error-in-wp-content-800x452.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px" /></a></p>\n<p>The bad news is that making this page look good, unless you know HTML, and returning the correct http status code so Google does not index this error page, which can screws up your SEO, is not so simple. First of all when you create a db-error.php, WordPress will use this page and return a http status code 200, which to Google means everything is fine. If Google is crawling your site when this happens that means Google will index your error page instead of your correct home page. This is bad. So to make sure Google does not index your custom WordPress database error page you need to include this at the top of your <strong>db-error.php</strong> file.<br />\n<code><br />\n&lt;?php header(''HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error''); ?&gt;<br />\n</code></p>\n<p>This will ensure your custom database error page will return the correct http status code so that search engines don&#8217;t index this page.</p>\n<p>To make this page look good you can use custom html and css to create page and make it look any way you want. That is if you know html. If not we have repurposed our <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/free-coming-soon-page/">free html coming soon page template</a> as an attractive alternate and it lets you collect email from your visitors so can notify them when your site is back up. This template uses <a href="http://mailchimp.com">MailChimp</a> to collect emails but you can swap that out for and 3rd party mail provider that provides an embeddable form.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note:</strong> Since WordPress is in error mode you will not be able to use another plugin or shortcode on your custom database error page. Just use HTML and CSS aside from the php http status code we provide above.</em></p>\n<h2>Free Customizable WordPress Database Connection Error Template</h2>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-error-template.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2337" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-error-template.jpg" alt="wordpress-database-error-template" width="940" height="780" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-error-template.jpg 940w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-error-template-400x332.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-error-template-768x637.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wordpress-database-error-template-800x664.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px" /></a></p>\n<p class="text-center">Get a free custom database error page template for your WordPress website to use when a database connection error occurs.</p>\n<div class="row">\n<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">\n<ul id="fcsp-features" class="list-unstyled">\n<li><strong>Features Include:</strong></li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-picture-o"></i>  Comes with 6 Background Images or Use Your Own</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-magic"></i>  Easily Customize the Logo, Headline and Description</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i>  Collect Emails with MailChimp</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-facebook-official"></i>  Display Links to Your Facebook, Twitter and Email Accounts</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-html5"></i>  Built with Bootstrap, HTML and CCS3</li>\n<li><i class="fa fa-question-circle-o"></i>  Well Documented</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class="btn btn-lg btn-seedprod btn-block" href="http://s.seedprod.com/wordpress-database-error-template"><i class="fa fa-cloud-download" style="color: #fff;"></i> Free Download</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Want to create a more customized error page and collect email from different email providers? Checkout <a href="http://comingsoonpage.com">http://comingsoonpage.com</a>, this builder creates custom html coming soon pages which can be repurposed for WordPress error pages.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-database-error-page-wordpress/">How to Create a Custom Database Error Page in WordPress with Free Template</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-custom-database-error-page-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2314";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"How to customize the WordPress Login Page";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 19 Oct 2016 15:01:03 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2293";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:551:"<p>The WordPress login page is pretty vanilla by default. If you look at it above, it&#8217;s not that interesting and comes heavily branded with WordPress. While this may be OK for some users most will want to at the very least change out the WordPress logo on the login page with their own logo or [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/">How to customize the WordPress Login Page</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6602:"<div id="attachment_2295" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2295" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-400x297.jpg" alt="The Default WordPress Login Page" width="400" height="297" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-400x297.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-768x570.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page-800x594.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/default-wordpress-login-page.jpg 823w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Default WordPress Login Page</p></div>\n<p>The WordPress login page is pretty vanilla by default. If you look at it above, it&#8217;s not that interesting and comes heavily branded with WordPress. While this may be OK for some users most will want to at the very least change out the WordPress logo on the login page with their own logo or their client&#8217;s logo. Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to easily customize the WordPress login page for any of your needs.</p>\n<h2>A Free WordPress Custom Login Page Plugin</h2>\n<p>The first plugin I want to show you is called <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login-page-wp/">Custom Login Page by SeedProd</a>. This is a free plugin which you can <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login-page-wp/">download</a> from WordPress.org and allows you to make of the most requested edits on the WordPress login page. After installing this plugin you can use the realtime customizer to edit most aspects of the login page. What&#8217;s nice about this is that you can see all your changes instantly. So say for example you want to change the WordPress login page logo. Simply use this plugin to insert your new logo and that&#8217;s it, done! In addition to being able to change out the logo you can also perform these edits on the login page.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Change the login page background color</li>\n<li>Add an image to the background and position that image in anyway</li>\n<li>Change the login button text</li>\n<li>Change the login page text colors, font size and typography</li>\n<li>Add custom css</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login-page-wp/screenshots/">Custom Login Page by SeedProd</a> WordPress plugin cover most users needs when it comes to simple edits on the WordPress login page. Here&#8217;s an example of a Custom WordPress Login page created with <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-login-page-wp/screenshots/">Custom Login Page by SeedProd</a></p>\n<div id="attachment_2301" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/screenshot-1.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2301" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/screenshot-1-400x238.jpg" alt="Custom Logo on the WordPress Login Page" width="400" height="238" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/screenshot-1-400x238.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/screenshot-1-768x457.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/screenshot-1-800x476.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/screenshot-1.jpg 1127w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Custom Logo, Background and Colors on the WordPress Login Page</p></div>\n<h2>A Paid WordPress Custom Login Page Plugin</h2>\n<p>If you need to do more advanced edits then check out the Pro Version of this plugin which is called <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-custom-login-page/">Login Page Pro by SeedProd</a> This plugin builds on the simplicity of the free version and adds the ability to customize more aspects of the WordPress Login Page. In addition to being able to perform all the edits you can in the free version you can also perform actions listed below on the login page.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Edit the Login Page Logo Alt Text and Logo Link</li>\n<li>Add a message above or below the login page form</li>\n<li>Change any of the text on the page page. For example change the Username/Email or Password Label.</li>\n<li>Add an color overlay to your background image</li>\n<li>Add a back ground slideshow or video on the login page</li>\n<li>Change the white login form back ground to any color or make it transparent.</li>\n<li>Change the position of the login form</li>\n<li>Change the color or any element on the WordPress login page</li>\n<li>Integrated with Google Fonts</li>\n<li>Add Social Media Profiles to the WordPress Login Page</li>\n<li>Add a Google Recaptcha to the WordPress Login Page</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So as you can see the Pro Version adds quite a few more advanced edit capabilities. Here&#8217;s an example of a WordPress Login page create with <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-custom-login-page/">Login Page Pro by SeedProd</a></p>\n<div id="attachment_2305" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-login-page.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2305" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-login-page-400x202.jpg" alt="Custom WordPress Login Page" width="400" height="202" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-login-page-400x202.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-login-page-768x388.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-login-page-800x404.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/custom-wordpress-login-page.jpg 1424w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Custom WordPress Login Page</p></div>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>As you can see customizing the WordPress page is easy and does not require a lot of skill or time. Like I said most users at the least will want to customize the logo. Are than any customizations you&#8217;d like to do on the WordPress Login page but not sure how to do? Let us know!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/">How to customize the WordPress Login Page</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-login-page/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2293";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"SeedProd Release Notes – October 2016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-release-notes-october-2016/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-release-notes-october-2016/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 17 Oct 2016 20:02:17 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Blog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2275";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:601:"<p>It&#8217;s been quite a while since we&#8217;ve sent a newsletter update so I wanted to fill you in on the latest happenings. We&#8217;ve been super busy since the beginning of the year making updates and improvements. Here&#8217;s what we&#8217;ve been up to! New Dashboard We&#8217;ve revamped our dashboard in an effort to make it easier to find [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-release-notes-october-2016/">SeedProd Release Notes &#8211; October 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10374:"<p>It&#8217;s been quite a while since we&#8217;ve sent a newsletter update so I wanted to fill you in on the latest happenings. We&#8217;ve been super busy since the beginning of the year making updates and improvements. Here&#8217;s what we&#8217;ve been up to!</p>\n<hr />\n<h2><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-39-50.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2277" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-39-50-800x506.jpg" alt="SeedProd New Dashboard" width="800" height="506" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-39-50-800x506.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-39-50-400x253.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-39-50-768x486.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-39-50.jpg 1286w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></h2>\n<h2>New Dashboard</h2>\n<p>We&#8217;ve revamped our dashboard in an effort to make it easier to find your active licenses along with the terms and docs. The default view should now show you your most recent active licenses and any license that has been upgraded or renewed should be hidden. If you see a license that is not hidden and that is no longer in use let us know and we can hide it. You can still view your complete order history and details under<strong> Purchase History &amp; Invoices.</strong></p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve also made it easier to see and manage which sites are licensed under the Manage Licensed Site section. When you deactivate a license it will now remotely deactivate a license on that website so you don&#8217;t have to manually deactivate on the site.</p>\n<p>Also now when you start a support ticket and type your subject we will auto suggest help topics to help you resolve your issue quicker.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-43-52.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2278" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-43-52-400x253.jpg" alt="SeedProd Support request" width="400" height="253" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-43-52-400x253.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-43-52-768x486.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-43-52-800x506.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-43-52.jpg 1286w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally we&#8217;ve update all our servers so everything should be zippy!</p>\n<hr />\n<p><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/realtime-page-builder-800x490-1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2281" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/realtime-page-builder-800x490-1-800x490.jpg" alt="realtime-page-builder-800x490-1" width="800" height="490" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/realtime-page-builder-800x490-1.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/realtime-page-builder-800x490-1-400x245.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/realtime-page-builder-800x490-1-768x470.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></p>\n<h2>Coming Soon Pro Version 5</h2>\n<p>Coming Soon Pro Version 5 is our biggest release yet and has been out since May. Version 5 is super stable and is our preferred version now. Learn more about <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/introducing-seedprod-coming-soon-pro-version-5/">SeedProd&#8217;s Coming Soon Pro Version 5&#8217;s features</a>. In addition we have also released two new Add Ons that let you create multiple coming soon/landing pages on one site and an Add On that lets you create you coming soon page in multiple languages. You can upgrade your current license in the members area to our new Developer License with Add On Package if you need this functionality.</p>\n<p>If you are starting a new website make sure to download the latest version from the <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/members">members area</a>. If you are still running version 4 and want to migrate to version 5 see this help article. <a href="http://support.seedprod.com/article/120-migrating-from-version-4-to-5">http://support.seedprod.com/article/120-migrating-from-version-4-to-5</a></p>\n<p>This will be the last time a manual migration will be required. We made the mistake of switching to a 3rd party settings framework in version 4 which cause many unforeseen issues. We rebuilt version 5 from the ground up to be our fastest most reliable version to date.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-59-35.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-2280" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-59-35-800x378.jpg" alt="MailChimp API Version 3 Support" width="800" height="378" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-59-35-800x378.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-59-35-400x189.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-59-35-768x363.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/2016-10-17_14-59-35.jpg 958w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></h2>\n<h2>MailChimp V3 API</h2>\n<p>This is only relative if you use MailChimp in out plugins. MailChimp is retiring Versions 1 and 2 of their api and requiring all developers to be using the latest version, Version 3, of their api by the start of the New Year. Version 3 support has been added to all our plugins and in the Coming Soon Page Pro Plugin since version 5.2.0. Any new installs automatically use version 3 of the MailChimp API and if you were using version 2 there will be a link in the MailChimp configuration to switch to Version 3. Make sure to test after you switch since some functionally has changed from version 2 to 3 of the MailChimp API.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the <a href="http://us12.campaign-archive2.com/?u=165abe0a1aa09263bc6ad1397&amp;id=13589911d7&amp;e=9530f68764">email from MailChimp</a> for more information.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-notification-bar/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2284" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-notification-bar-pro.jpg" alt="seeprod-bottom-ad-notification-bar-pro" width="700" height="150" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-notification-bar-pro.jpg 700w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-notification-bar-pro-400x86.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></h2>\n<h2>New Notification Bar Plugin</h2>\n<p>We have released a new notification bar plugin that makes it support easy to display notices, collect emails and created time based calls to action on your website. Learn more about our <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-404-page-pro/">WordPress Notification Bar Plugin</a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-custom-login-page/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2285" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-login-page-pro.jpg" alt="seeprod-bottom-ad-login-page-pro" width="700" height="150" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-login-page-pro.jpg 700w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-login-page-pro-400x86.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></h2>\n<h2>New Login Page Plugin</h2>\n<p>We have also released a plugin that makes it super easy to customize the default WordPress login page. Add a logo, change colors, fonts, text and more. It uses our realtime customizer we originally built for our Coming Soon Plugin and makes changes to your WordPress Login page fast and easy. Learn More about our <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-custom-login-page/">WordPress Login Page Customizer Plugin</a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wordpress-404-page-pro/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2286" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-404-page-pro.jpg" alt="seeprod-bottom-ad-404-page-pro" width="700" height="150" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-404-page-pro.jpg 700w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/seeprod-bottom-ad-404-page-pro-400x86.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a></h2>\n<h2>Update to the 404 Page Plugin</h2>\n<p>We have updated our custom 404 page plugin to use our new realtime customize as well. You can download Version 2 from the <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/members">members area</a>. Currently the is not a way to migrate settings from version 1 to 2 but there will be by the end of the year.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>What&#8217;s Next</h2>\n<p>One of the most requested features is the ability to collect more data than just name and email. I&#8217;m working to get a new Form Builder Add On that I hope to have out by the end of the year that will let you do just that.</p>\n<p>More themes for the Coming Soon Page Pro Plugin. I will be releasing a new theme each week next year for the Coming Soon Plugin to build up our theme library and to help you get started quickly.</p>\n<p>Plus a few more features I can share at the moment. ;)</p>\n<p>We released <a href="http://comingsoonpage.com">http://comingsoonpage.com</a> this year which let&#8217;s you create html coming soon pages you can use on any site and not just WordPress sites. We will be adding this into our new upcoming SeedProd Site Membership that will give you access to all our plugins and services for a low yearly price. More about this to come.</p>\n<p>We also have a few more plugins planned for 2017.</p>\n<p>Got a idea or feature request, <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/contact/">let us know</a>!</p>\n<p>Cheers,<br />\nJohn from SeedProd</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-release-notes-october-2016/">SeedProd Release Notes &#8211; October 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-release-notes-october-2016/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2275";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"How to disable the Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"https://www.seedprod.com/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"https://www.seedprod.com/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 14 Jun 2016 17:13:01 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2039";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:591:"<p>When you sign up for a new Bluehost, HostGator or other web hosting account and start a new WordPress site, the host may automatically install the Mojo Marketplace Plugin. This plugin gives you access to the Mojo Marketplace which sells plugins and themes but it will also install a Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page on your [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page/">How to disable the Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6959:"<p>When you sign up for a new <a class="thirstylink" href="https://www.seedprod.com/go/bluehost/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Bluehost</a>, <a href="http://hostgator.com">HostGator</a> or other web hosting account and start a new WordPress site, the host may automatically install the Mojo Marketplace Plugin. This plugin gives you access to the Mojo Marketplace which sells plugins and themes but it will also install a Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page on your website so that when visitors view your website they will see image below instead of your website under construction.</p>\n<div style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page.jpg"><img class="wp-image-2215 size-medium" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-400x278.jpg" alt="Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page" width="400" height="278" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-400x278.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-768x533.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-800x555.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page.jpg 1287w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page</p></div>\n<p>It&#8217;s not obvious to some users how to remove or disable this page or plugin so I&#8217;ll walk you through the process.</p>\n<p><strong>To disable the Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Log into your Admin Area on your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Visit the Dashboard and at the top there is a notification that says:<br />\n<em>&#8220;Your site is currently displaying a &#8220;Coming Soon&#8221; page. Once you are ready to launch your site <strong>click here</strong>.&#8221;</em><br />\n<a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page.jpg"><br />\n</a><a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2222 size-large" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-800x625.jpg" alt="Disable Mojo Marketplace Notification Link" width="800" height="625" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-800x625.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-400x312.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page-768x600.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page.jpg 1119w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></li>\n<li>Click the link in the notification and the Coming Soon Page will then be removed and disabled from your website. <strong>Note:</strong> You may need to clear any caching plugins or your host cache.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>To disable the Mojo Marketplace Plugin</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Log into your Admin Area on your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Plugins</strong> &gt; <strong>Installed Plugins</strong> to view your current installed plugins.<br />\n<a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/remove-mojo-marketplace.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2223 size-large" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/remove-mojo-marketplace-800x283.jpg" alt="remove-mojo-marketplace" width="800" height="283" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/remove-mojo-marketplace-800x283.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/remove-mojo-marketplace-400x141.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/remove-mojo-marketplace-768x272.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/remove-mojo-marketplace.jpg 936w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></li>\n<li>Find the <strong>Mojo Marketplace</strong> plugin in your installed plugin list and click <strong>Deactivate<br />\n<a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2224 size-large" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-800x283.jpg" alt="Disable Mojo Marketplace" width="800" height="283" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-800x283.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-400x141.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace-768x272.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/disable-mojo-marketplace.jpg 936w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></strong></li>\n<li>Optionally you can then click <strong>Delete</strong> to completely remove the <strong>Mojo Marketplace</strong> plugin.<br />\n<a href="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delete-mojo-marketplace-plugin.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2225 size-large" src="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delete-mojo-marketplace-plugin-800x108.jpg" alt="Delete the Mojo Marketplace Plugin" width="800" height="108" srcset="https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delete-mojo-marketplace-plugin-800x108.jpg 800w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delete-mojo-marketplace-plugin-400x54.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delete-mojo-marketplace-plugin-768x104.jpg 768w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delete-mojo-marketplace-plugin.jpg 814w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a></li>\n<li>Again you may need to clear any caching plugins or your host cache.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! Most hosts will have an option to disable the auto install of the Mojo Marketplace plugin which will prevent future installs of WordPress from displaying the Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page. Check with your host for that option.</p>\n<p>If you are looking for a Coming Soon Page that offers more options like themes, collecting emails, countdown, social sharing option and more be sure to check out our <a href="https://www.seedprod.com">Coming Soon Page</a> plugin for WordPress.  Not using WordPress? No problem, then checkout <a href="http://h">https://comingsoonpage .com</a> which creates a pure <a href="https://www.comingsoonpage.com">html Coming Soon Page</a> which you can use on most any site or platform.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page/">How to disable the Mojo Marketplace Coming Soon Page</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"https://www.seedprod.com/disable-mojo-marketplace-coming-soon-page/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"3";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2039";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Introducting Zapier Integration with the Coming Soon Page Pro Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://www.seedprod.com/zapier-integration-coming-soon-page/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://www.seedprod.com/zapier-integration-coming-soon-page/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 02 Jun 2016 19:36:46 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2194";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:602:"<p>Want to create a Coming Soon Page and collect emails and send them to your favorite Email Marking Services? The Coming Soon Page Pro plugin for WordPress has been making this easy for the past 5 years and we have had integrations with over 15 email marketing services. Inevitably however we are always getting new integration [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/zapier-integration-coming-soon-page/">Introducting Zapier Integration with the Coming Soon Page Pro Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1225:"<p>Want to create a Coming Soon Page and collect emails and send them to your favorite Email Marking Services? The Coming Soon Page Pro plugin for WordPress has been making this easy for the past 5 years and we have had <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/features/">integrations</a> with over 15 email marketing services. Inevitably however we are always getting new integration requests and questions about whether we integrate with X. We are now proud to announce that we have and integration with <a href="https://zapier.com">Zapier</a> which makes it a since to integrate with over 500 services (and not just email marketing services).</p>\n<p>Explore all the service you can connect with here:  <a href="https://zapier.com/zapbook/">https://zapier.com/zapbook/</a></p>\n<p>See how to setup Zapier: <a href="http://support.seedprod.com/article/131-zapier-integration">http://support.seedprod.com/article/131-zapier-integration</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/zapier-integration-coming-soon-page/">Introducting Zapier Integration with the Coming Soon Page Pro Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://www.seedprod.com/zapier-integration-coming-soon-page/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2194";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Introducing the new Animated Particle Theme for Coming Soon Page Pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"https://www.seedprod.com/introducing-the-new-animated-particle-theme-for-coming-soon-page-pro/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:102:"https://www.seedprod.com/introducing-the-new-animated-particle-theme-for-coming-soon-page-pro/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 02 Jun 2016 15:24:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=2196";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:631:"<p>We are proud to introduce our latest theme for the Coming Soon Page Pro plugin. It&#8217;s called Particle and features an animated background thanks to the particle.js script. Easily change the background color or add an image. And of course it comes free with any active license of the Coming Soon Page pro plugin. Check [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/introducing-the-new-animated-particle-theme-for-coming-soon-page-pro/">Introducing the new Animated Particle Theme for Coming Soon Page Pro</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"John Turner";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1269:"<p>We are proud to introduce our latest theme for the <a href="https://www.seedprod.com">Coming Soon Page Pro</a> plugin. It&#8217;s called <strong>Particle</strong> and features an animated background thanks to the <a href="https://github.com/VincentGarreau/particles.js/">particle.js</a> script. Easily change the background color or add an image. And of course it comes free with any active <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/pricing/">license</a> of the Coming Soon Page pro plugin. Check out some of our other <a href="https://www.seedprod.com/themes/">Coming Soon Page themes</a>.</p>\n<p>Want a particular kind of theme? Let us know if the comments.</p>\n<p><iframe class=''youtube-player'' type=''text/html'' width=''640'' height=''390'' src=''https://www.youtube.com/embed/OsSWAVfXAzE?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;fs=1&#038;autohide=2&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;wmode=transparent'' allowfullscreen=''true'' style=''border:0;''></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com/introducing-the-new-animated-particle-theme-for-coming-soon-page-pro/">Introducing the new Animated Particle Theme for Coming Soon Page Pro</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.seedprod.com">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:99:"https://www.seedprod.com/introducing-the-new-animated-particle-theme-for-coming-soon-page-pro/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:7:"post-id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"2196";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:30:"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1";a:1:{s:4:"site";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"d