 stains because there are substances that permanently discolor the carpet. The age of the carpet and other factors come into play here, but we try to remove all spots and stains.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Question:</strong> There are bubbles and ripples in my carpet after it was cleaned. Is this normal?\n\n<strong>Answer:</strong> The bubbles and ripples should flatten on their own within a few days; however this is a sign that the carpet should have been stretched prior to cleaning. Please contact us as soon as possible if the the bubbles or ripples don''t go away: (989) 339-4205\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Question:</strong> Will carpet cleaning get rid of pests like fleas?\n\n<strong>Answer:</strong> We encourage you to kill all adult fleas and pests before carpet cleaning. A professional exterminator may be of more assistance in this matter. Fleas and other pests may lay eggs in other areas as well, so you may consider having all upholstery, area rugs, and pet beds treated and cleaned\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a class="', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-12-07 13:44:40', '2016-12-07 18:44:40', '', 95, 'http://muddybootscarpetcleaning.com/95-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(99, 1, '2016-12-07 11:55:15', '2016-12-07 16:55:15', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions:</h2>\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Do I need to vacuum before you come?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> Nope. Our powerful cleaning equipment will handle all of that\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Will the cleaning chemicals harm my children or pets?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> We use only certified, professional cleaning chemicals that are safe for children and pets (and adults too)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> How long will it take my carpets to dry after you clean them?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> Our machines are very powerful and vacuum up most of the moisture. However, the carpet will still be damp to the touch. Using fans or home heating/cooling will help the carpets dry faster\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Can I walk on the carpets right after you clean them?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> You sure can! Just not in your street shoes, and be careful not to slip when walking from carpet to another floor\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Do you move furniture?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> We sure do! There''s no extra charge to move furniture\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Does carpet cleaning make my carpet soil faster?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> This usually occurs because of soap residue left in the carpet during the cleaning process. Our special cleaning formula and powerful hot water extraction process removes all of the soap residue, so this isn''t a concern\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Some spots reappeared after having my carpets cleaned. Is this normal?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> Some substances from the carpet backing may wick to the surface during the cleaning / drying process. Please contact us as soon as possible if this happens: (989) 339-4205\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Do you guarantee removal of all spots and stains?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> We cannot guarantee the removal of 100% of all spots and stains because there are substances that permanently discolor the carpet. The age of the carpet and other factors come into play here, but we try to remove all spots and stains.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> There are bubbles and ripples in my carpet after it was cleaned. Is this normal?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> The bubbles and ripples should flatten on their own within a few days; however this is a sign that the carpet should have been stretched prior to cleaning. Please contact us as soon as possible if the the bubbles or ripples don''t go away: (989) 339-4205\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Question:</strong> Will carpet cleaning get rid of pests like fleas?\r\n\r\n<strong>Answer:</strong> We encourage you to kill all adult fleas and pests before carpet cleaning. A professional exterminator may be of more assistance in this matter. Fleas and other pests may lay eggs in other areas as well, so you may consider having all upholstery, area rugs, and pet beds treated and cleaned\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-07 11:55:15', '2016-12-07 16:55:15', '', 95, 'http://muddybootscarpetcleaning.com/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
